cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

The paper discusses the benefits of using sparse representations in artificial networks, which is a topic closely related to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the potential benefits of sparsity on accuracy and noise robustness, which are topics related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The simulations conducted on MNIST and the Google Speech Command Dataset also suggest that the paper may fall under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the potential benefits of sparsity on computational efficiency and power requirements, which are topics related to systems and control (cs.SY).
